page.title: 04WEEKEND, LINFORD M. KEYNES
page.content: A girl aged 11; the weekend of Friday 17th to Sunday 19th May 1985. Friday evening- returned from school- watched television, Sons and Daughters (an Australian series)- played outside or house with friends on a climbing frame and swings. Tea at 5.30 p.m. I made the coffee and washed up afterwards. Later played tennis at Newport Pagnell. Saturday- went to Stantonbury Music Centre- played on flute with orchestra. 10.30 a.m. returned home and made mum some flans to put in the freezer. 3 p.m. watched F>A> Cup Final on television- Manchester United beat Everton 1-0. Later played out with friends and watched 'Dynasty' on television. Sunday- read for 2 hours-got up at 10.30 a.m. and went to church. Took some furniture to my sister's new flat in Conniburrow. Rest of day spent eating and watching T.V.
